### Tested versions

- Reproducible in 4.5.dev4

### System information

Godot v4.5.dev (4a5575534) - macOS Sequoia (15.4.1) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Metal (Forward+) - integrated Apple M4 Max (Apple9) - Apple M4 Max (14 threads)

### Issue description

When opening certain windows such as the editor or project settings or search for help on macOS in a new project, the window opens somewhere on the secondary monitor instead of in the center of the main monitor.

The issue seems to be the position that is passed to  the `Window::popup`. The Rect2i of the first screen doesn't have the position and so it uses the next screen instead. 

```
void Window::popup(const Rect2i &p_screen_rect) {
        // ....
	int scr = DisplayServer::get_singleton()->get_screen_count();
	for (int i = 0; i < scr; i++) {
		Rect2i r = DisplayServer::get_singleton()->screen_get_usable_rect(i);

		if (r.has_point(position)) {
			current_screen = i;
			break;
		}
	}
        // ....
}
```

As you can see in this video, when I press F1 to open the search menu, the window doens't appear on my screen with Godot. 

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e2fb1cf6-552e-4952-9995-213197fd5e69)

### Steps to reproduce

1. Have multiple monitors
2. Open project settings or editor settings in a new project in a new project
3. The window will open on a secondary monitor

